enhanced_by.reason: Both methods modify the internal state of the CompositeMap by adding or removing maps.
Both methods involve removing a map from the composite, which can affect the behavior of the remove method.
The remove method returns the value associated with the key if it exists, similar to how containsKey checks for the existence of a key.
Both methods return the value associated with a key, making them useful for constructing assertions about the state of the map after removal.
